"```sql\nSELECT \n  (COUNT(CASE WHEN client.gender = 'M' THEN 1 END) * 100.0 / COUNT(client.client_id)) AS percentage_male_clients\nFROM \n  client\nJOIN \n  account ON client.district_id = account.district_id\nJOIN \n  district ON account.district_id = district.district_id\nWHERE \n  district.A3 = 'south Bohemia'\nORDER BY \n  CAST(district.A4 AS INTEGER) DESC\nLIMIT 1;\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the percentage of male clients for the branch located in the south Bohemia region with the largest number of inhabitants. It uses a `JOIN` to connect the `client`, `account`, and `district` tables based on their foreign key relationships. The query filters for the region 'south Bohemia', orders the results by the number of inhabitants in descending order, and limits the result to the branch with the largest population."